                        </origin>
                        <provenance type="found">Small amount of ogham recorded in sketch in Archaeologia volume iv 1776. May be in Gough's Camden. Original location recorded in 1777 'standing upright at <foreign xml:lang="cy">Pen y Mynidd</foreign>' (or <foreign xml:lang="cy">Pen-y-mynydd</foreign>) and 'a little distance from the Caer...Madre' but unclear where this was. Moved to <foreign xml:lang="cy">Fedw Hir</foreign> house near <foreign xml:lang="cy">Aberd√¢r</foreign> before 1894. The stone is locally-sourced medium-grained sandstone. 
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance type="observed" source="RED2007"><ref target="https://www.visitmerthyr.co.uk/things-to-do/attractions/cyfarthfa-museum-art-gallery/">Cyfarthfa Museum, Merthyr Tydfil.</ref>
